    <law type="statute"><section><amendatorysection chaptername="State Administrative Departments" statutenumber="81-5,171" amended="yes"><bookinfo>Revised Statutes Cumulative Supplement, 2020</bookinfo><statuteno>81-5,171</statuteno><catchline>Excessive pressure prohibited.</catchline><para>The owner, user, or person or persons in charge of any boiler required to be inspected by the Boiler Inspection Act shall not allow or permit a greater pressure in any unit than is stated in the certificate of inspection issued by the inspector.</para></amendatorysection></section><source><para>Laws 1943, c. 112, &#167; 2(4), p. 393; </para><para>R.S.1943, &#167; 48-705; </para><para>R.S.1943, (1984), &#167; 48-705; </para><para>Laws 1987, LB 462, &#167; 7; </para><para>Laws 1995, LB 438, &#167; 5; </para><para>R.S.1943, (2010), &#167; 48-725; </para><para>Laws 2019, LB301, &#167; 7. </para></source></law>
